                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Dark roast can be great—especially if you like a bolder, more roasty flavor.\n\nIf you want recommendations, tell me how you usually drink it:\n- **Brewing method** (espresso, drip, French press, pour-over, etc.)\n- **With or without milk/sugar**\n- Flavor preference: **chocolatey/nutty**, **smoky**, or **low-acid/smooth**\n\nIn general:\n- For a **smooth, chocolatey dark roast**, look for **“French roast,” “Italian roast,”** or tasting notes like **cocoa, bittersweet chocolate, molasses**.\n- If you want **less bitterness**, try a **fresh dark roast** (recent roast date) and brew slightly cooler or a bit shorter.\n- If you like **espresso-style intensity**, Italian-roast espresso blends tend to match that profile well.",
